The article discusses Vice President Harris' leadership in the Root Causes Strategy, which aims to address the economic, governance, and security issues driving irregular migration from Central America. The strategy combines government resources with private sector investments to support the long-term development of the region. Vice President Harris has met with regional leaders and traveled to Guatemala, Mexico, and Honduras to launch new initiatives. Through her Call to Action initiative, she has brought together private sector leaders and generated over $1.2 billion in commitments to create jobs and opportunities in the region. The Biden-Harris Administration is making progress in creating hope for people in El Salvador, Guatemala, and Honduras to find a better life at home.